Slice `007H3-frozen-case-provenance-and-read-scope-parity-closure` is complete and ready for independent Ralph validation.

Implemented:

- Existing approval cycles validate exclusively against frozen case provenance, never mutable live appraisal rows.
- Case collection/detail, actions, sanction decisions, and Credit Sanction Register now share frozen-validity and actor-scope decisions before counts, filters, or pagination.
- Malformed frozen cases fail closed even when the stored coherence flag and reader index remain stale and true.
- Returned cycle 1 retains its original provenance and review facts while corrected cycle 2 freezes its own facts.
- No model-save signal, hidden cross-table write, migration, dependency, or frontend production change was introduced.
- API contracts, Epic 007 digest, 007I, and 007J were updated with the delivered semantics.

